history.content: The paragraph next to the "3" in the informational document on swap addresses your specific scenario, I believe.

I'm currently enrolled in course A, and would like to take course B instead (which is full). A and B during the same time period. Would the swap feature allow to me automatically drop A if i get into B? I know how swap works, but my thinking is that since they conflict, I'll never get off of B's waitlist (since you can't get off a waitlist if it conflicts with an enrolled class), and therefore the swap will never be initiated. Does anyone know if that's true?

Edit: resolved
